Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.72,0:00:15.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.56,0:00:20.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you burn down our village!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.23,0:00:22.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.90,0:00:25.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.63,0:00:51.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.18,0:00:58.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.82,0:01:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Revenge for the Earl of Altirk!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.53,0:01:20.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll beat you all down!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:23.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Black Prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.46,0:01:25.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat!\NDisperse, and flee into the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.21,0:01:27.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.96,0:01:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about me and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.67,0:01:37.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to the castle, and help Sir Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:43.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Altirk forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.70,0:01:58.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No need to chase them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.03,0:02:02.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The detached unit was routed by the witches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.37,0:02:06.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll regroup, and resume our advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:20.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This area appears to be a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:21.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How impudent!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.97,0:02:26.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The path's diverging in different directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.48,0:02:30.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They must be using this thorny undergrowth\Nto open and shut the pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.40,0:02:33.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Theo's aim?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.07,0:02:37.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His plan is probably to toy with our men,\Nand split us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.03,0:02:41.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cunning of him.\NJust keep heading toward the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:27.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:31.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Being desert people, they must have had a hard\Ntime navigating this Demonic territory's forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:35.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro! Come out from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.61,0:04:37.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you on in a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.90,0:04:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time,\NPrince of Dartania, Milza Kuches!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.32,0:04:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've won this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.62,0:04:47.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should leave this forest right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.28,0:04:51.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When night falls,\Nthis forest's appearance changes even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.62,0:04:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It begins to writhe in search of human blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:57.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then be holed up in that castle forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:05:01.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, I'll eliminate\Nevery nation in the Altirk Treaty!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.43,0:05:05.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All forces, retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.98,0:05:15.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that he'd attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.81,0:05:19.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Telius Savoie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:24.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't all that proficient at magic,\Nbut he was brilliant at military strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:29.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that his scheme wasn't botched,\Nrather it was taken out of his hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:31.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:37.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next battle will be grueling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:38.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.34,0:05:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that Theo Cornaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:45.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Forest of Eternal Darkness\Nis Demon territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.97,0:05:49.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a suitable station for a military force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.14,0:05:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro only has\Ntwo choices available to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.35,0:05:55.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One is to return his troops to Bulltava.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:56.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the other?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.73,0:06:01.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To emerge from the Forest of Eternal Darkness,\Nand attack this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:07.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he does that,\Nhe'll be playing right into my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.86,0:06:09.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This time I'll obliterate him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.53,0:06:14.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would you think\Nof sending troops to Regalia?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:16.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the south? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:22.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To show the Altirk Treaty Lords\Nthat our forces are still powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and to ward off an assault from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.84,0:06:29.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time,\Nwe will attempt to draw out Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:35.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So as soon as Theo comes sauntering out,\Nwe'll rush back and vanquish him, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:39.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good. Start your preparations at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.44,0:06:40.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.44,0:06:45.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were outmaneuvered\Nin the Forest of Eternal Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:50.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Siluca Meletes.\NThat won't happen this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.66,0:06:55.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:07:01.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, Milza has invaded Regalia\Nwith 7,000 men in tow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.09,0:07:04.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he's ignoring us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:08.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milza is probably trying to lure you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So he wants to crush us on the ground\Nonce we emerge from the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.64,0:07:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, I think we should\Ngo along with his scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.64,0:07:23.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that morale is high after our victory in the\NForest of Eternal Darkness, we can't let this go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:26.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We must seek aid from the citizens of Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.57,0:07:34.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll have to command\Na volunteer army again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:37.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milza will curse me when we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.58,0:07:43.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I liberated Sistina,\NI called on the people to rise up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:48.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I may have put an end to the Rossini's reign,\Nbut many people lost their lives in that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:55.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, I believe that you can hear\Nthe people's silent voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.22,0:08:00.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it's you who puts them into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.52,0:08:03.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:08.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head to Castle Unicorn in full force!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.32,0:08:17.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The citizens of Altirk haven't accepted\NDartania's rule. There's no question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.00,0:08:25.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Though I do feel that attacking\NCastle Unicorn would be reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.42,0:08:29.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you feel that way,\Nthen come join us in Altirk right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.51,0:08:31.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That can't happen just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:35.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you just not emerge\Nfrom the Forest of Eternal Darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.10,0:08:40.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Sir Theo does nothing\Nwhile Dartania attacks Regalia,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.98,0:08:45.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the citizens of Altirk will be disheartened,\Nand they won't rise up for us.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.77,0:08:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.32,0:08:52.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our only window of opportunity to attack\NCastle Unicorn is now, while Milza is away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.78,0:08:57.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Milza returns before our forces can assemble,\Nit'll become a painful battle for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.37,0:09:01.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In other words,\Nwe just need to buy you some time?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.62,0:09:02.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.62,0:09:07.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\NThen I'll have Sir Selge buy you that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:14.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I have a strategy in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:19.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to report, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.60,0:09:21.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A white flag has been hoisted\Nover the Regalian castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:23.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.89,0:09:28.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the Earl of Regalia and his younger brother,\NViscount Igor, have slipped out of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.61,0:09:29.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.90,0:09:33.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's a ploy to draw us out\Nby pretending to have fled?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:37.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,People had begun\Nrioting and looting inside the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.41,0:09:41.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we've captured\Nthe Earl of Regalia's contracted mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:44.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems she'd been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:46.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He left his contracted mage behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:48.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So he really ran away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.04,0:09:52.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Theo Cornaro\Nwas recently victorious over us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.38,0:09:55.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Selge Constance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.88,0:09:58.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder he's known as the Fleeing Earl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:04.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This just means that Theo\Nisn't a Lord worthy of Selge's trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.85,0:10:07.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In Selge's eyes,\NTheo is a wandering Lord who Villar took in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:11.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.07,0:10:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't leave things as-is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:19.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, Lassic David, the king of Sievis, will\Narrive with reinforcements to reclaim the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.70,0:10:21.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll prepare to subjugate them immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:23.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you give me a week, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:25.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not fast enough. Do it in five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.17,0:10:28.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.98,0:10:47.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:49.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.98,0:10:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Theo Cornaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.65,0:10:58.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did he actually sacrifice Regalia\Nto buy himself some time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.57,0:11:03.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, to think that he gathered\Nthis many soldiers in a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.37,0:11:07.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So he still has his one skill\Nof being able to exhort the masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.58,0:11:11.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care how enormous his army may be.\NAfter all, it's only a ragtag force!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.38,0:11:15.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll clash with them head on,\Nand obliterate them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.26,0:11:22.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since we left some troops in Regalia,\Nwe're down to 5,000 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.05,0:11:26.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Theo appears to have close to 50,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.27,0:11:30.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let us return to the impregnable Castle Unicorn,\Nand wait for reinforcements to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.23,0:11:31.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.73,0:11:34.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would be foolish to battle\Nunder such unfavorable circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:38.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We must summon reinforcements\Nfrom Waldlind, Starck, and Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:41.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The final battle can wait\Nuntil after we've gathered sufficient troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.87,0:11:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to flee into the castle\Nwithout fighting a single battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.88,0:11:54.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you, please restrain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:03.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:08.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.94,0:12:16.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro has surrounded\NCastle Unicorn with a huge army?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.44,0:12:19.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Furthermore, all the Altirk Treaty Lords\Nand their troops
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:23.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are assembling under the command\Nof Lassic, king of Sievis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:28.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the Earl of Le Couleurs is being\Nmore persistent than we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.58,0:12:32.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If by chance that Milza is defeated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.08,0:12:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that will leave Waldlind under attack\Nfrom both the north and the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.38,0:12:40.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go to Milza's aid with 3,000 of my knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.97,0:12:42.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro is a dangerous Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.43,0:12:46.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Left unchecked, who knows\Nhow big of a threat he'll become.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.77,0:12:55.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Considering Prince Milza's situation, I believe\Nthat a force of that size would be insufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:58.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we do need to prepare for Earl Le Couleurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.44,0:13:00.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the most I can offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.78,0:13:02.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely there will be reinforcements\Nfrom Dartania as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.24,0:13:09.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to strongly urge\NLady Ulrica to go to his aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.96,0:13:16.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That lame Milza!\NAfter all that blustering, look at him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.04,0:13:21.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've received a request from Lady Marrine\Nto provide Sir Milza with reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:24.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not until we've subjugated Haman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:27.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we're late joining the battle,\Nwe'll be viewed negatively.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:33.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can take care of Haman in three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.94,0:13:39.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After plundering Starck,\Nand taking everything from Haman,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:41.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'll have stockpiled plenty of funds and food!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.69,0:13:45.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep seizing territories and court ranks\Nlike there's no tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:51.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's not Marrine who'll be emperor,\Nbut my father Erik!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:59.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A report came in that a fleet from Nord\Nis closing in on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.13,0:14:05.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After taking so much from me,\Ntheir final move is to rob me of my lands?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.97,0:14:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The coffers are empty now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:13.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the only decent clothes I have\Nis this one dress that my husbands gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.27,0:14:16.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sollas... Joachim..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:23.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The men who I loved put their lives on the line\Nto fight for me and for Haman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.03,0:14:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it looks like I'll lose everything after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:30.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a foregone conclusion just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.08,0:14:35.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Starck has brought along 2,000 slave soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that a Lord serving under\Nthe Earl of Sistina has infiltrated their ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.59,0:14:43.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Lord, doing a Shadow-like job?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.76,0:14:48.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's Sir Juzel, the head of the Rossini family,\Nformer rulers of Sistina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.51,0:14:51.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll work with him,\Nand get the slave soldiers on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.39,0:14:53.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.52,0:14:59.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The slaves' discontent in Starck has been growing,\Nand I hear the situation is becoming critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.31,0:15:05.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll appeal to them by announcing a major\Nslave uprising has broken out in Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.99,0:15:09.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've arranged to have Sir Juzel\Nrespond to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.95,0:15:11.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Haman is a small nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.99,0:15:16.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we get every slave to ally with us,\NI don't see us winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:21.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to follow the Earl of Sistina,\Nand have the citizens work with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.09,0:15:28.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}After all, they do know that you've emptied\Nthe nation's coffers in order to protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:34.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They probably see me as a pathetic ruler\Nwho can't do anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.64,0:15:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Lords and the soldiers have probably\Nlost faith in me by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.77,0:15:40.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:43.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone here admires\Nhow uninhibited you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:49.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}If you make a move, Haman will unite,\Nand fight the Nords with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.32,0:15:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you really think so?\N- Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And to have it become more certain,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.87,0:16:01.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Eudokia, would you please\Nremove those clothes you're wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.29,0:16:04.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.79,0:16:09.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Haman's Lords and soldiers have assembled\Nin the courtyard of the royal palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.22,0:16:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll remove that dress in front of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.14,0:16:15.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and exemplify that our country's wealth\Nhas been depleted,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:19.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and get them to determine that to protect\Nour lands and people, the only option is to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.23,0:16:23.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to get naked in public?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:27.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still have a very attractive physique.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:31.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain that your Lords, your soldiers,\Nand your people will all be inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:35.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I give up right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.83,0:16:40.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to face my husbands,\Nwho gave their lives for both me and Haman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.09,0:16:50.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, will be accompanying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:53.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}If I were to go out there wearing clothes,\Nit won't be convincing to request their resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.53,0:17:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Eudokia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.79,0:17:26.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Selam.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.25,0:17:28.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Selam!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:33.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have relinquished everything\Nto the people of Nord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.30,0:17:39.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The coffers are now empty, and I no longer\Nhave any fortune to dispose of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:42.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yet they're still trying to rob us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.35,0:17:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of our nation's territories, and its people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.27,0:17:49.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But those are things I will not give them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.03,0:17:58.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Towards that end, I will gladly give up\Nmy life, the last thing that remains!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.79,0:18:03.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For Lady Eudokia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.67,0:18:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give my life for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:12.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.88,0:18:15.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will fight by your side, Lady Eudokia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.31,0:18:23.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:31.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:35.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.03,0:18:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We, the people of Haman,\Nhave given you everything we have!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.62,0:18:42.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we will not become your slaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.79,0:18:48.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means losing our lives,\Nwe will choose freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:51.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty defiant for someone who's naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:53.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the people of Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:18:58.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A full-scale uprising\Nwill soon explode in your homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.05,0:19:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be long before Starck is liberated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:07.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so there's no longer any reason\Nfor you to obey the Nords!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.89,0:19:10.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- What kind of nonsense is—\N- She's absolutely right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.52,0:19:11.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:13.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the queen of Haman!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:17.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the state we, the people of Starck,\Nfind ourselves in now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.20,0:19:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Robbed of all we own,\Nwe might as well be buck naked!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.20,0:19:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.33,0:19:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody shut that guy up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.58,0:19:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the queen is ready to give her life\Nto protect her people's freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.38,0:19:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The opponents we should be fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.42,0:19:35.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are not the brave citizens of Haman,\Nbut the plunderers from Nord!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.72,0:19:38.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's follow the queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:41.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.35,0:19:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sound the horn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.01,0:19:47.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both the Haman army and the slave soldiers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.06,0:19:48.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.85,0:19:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Ulrica, I've received word that\Na slave rebellion has broken out all across Starck!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.65,0:19:56.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come, let us fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.78,0:19:58.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- That's not possible!\N- Please fall back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all lies concocted by the Haman queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:06.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it is true, our retreat will be cut off,\Nand we'll be annihilated!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:10.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Let me go! If I let this happen,\NI can't look at my father in the eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.46,0:20:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, evacuate! Return to your ships!\NWe're retreating to Starck!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.09,0:20:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't decide stuff without me!\NI refuse to run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.86,0:20:36.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Where the hell are the reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.15,0:20:43.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine is on her way here with 3,000\NWaldlind Knights under her command.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:46.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we launch an assault\Nfrom the castle when they arrive,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.08,0:20:48.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we can weaken\Nthe position of Theo's army.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:54.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Worker Ant Petr?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:58.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He built that in less than a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:20:59.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.09,0:21:03.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy has established a stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.80,0:21:08.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Margrave of Waldlind comes\Nto back us up, it won't be that easy to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.97,0:21:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Lady Marrine is killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:16.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both Dartania and Lady Ulrica\Nare sending us reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.06,0:21:16.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.86,0:21:18.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been able to contact them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.57,0:21:21.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, not yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:28.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There were some battles I couldn't win,\Nbut I've never once lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.33,0:21:31.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yet now,\NI'm on the brink of defeat for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.83,0:21:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And with this single defeat,\NI could lose everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.71,0:21:42.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Vexing as it may be, right now all I can do\Nis trust that my allies will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:48.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,OUTPOST
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.48,0:23:19.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reporting!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.02,0:23:22.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The army of Lassic, king of Sievis, has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.40,0:23:26.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have about 30,000 soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 17\NTWO HEROES
